## Implemented: Phase 2 (Admin Review + Permissions)
- Added admin-only dashboard tab: `Admin Requests` (visible only for users with `manage_options`).
- Admin tab includes:
	- List of submitted requests with owner and current status.
	- Direct `Review / Edit` action per request.
	- Full editable form for selected request.
- Admin can update:
	- Request status (`submitted`, `in_review`, `completed`)
	- Business intro/details
	- Business type
	- Legal status
	- Full-service toggle and goals
	- Service lines (service type, multi-actions, detailed description)
	- Add more service lines dynamically
- Security:
	- Admin update action protected by nonce.
	- Edit UI/action available only for admin users (`manage_options`).
- UX:
	- Dashboard can auto-open the correct tab via `dashboard_tab` query or URL hash.
	- Admin form remains on admin tab after save/validation.
- Header dashboard action continues to open custom `/dashboard` route, not default WP admin dashboard UI.

## Implemented: Phase 2.1 Fixes
- Client status-change notifications added in dashboard overview:
	- When admin changes request status, client sees a status update notification in dashboard.
	- Notification is marked as read after display.
- Admin Review/Edit navigation hardened:
	- Replaced direct query link with GET form submit button for `Review / Edit` action.
	- This avoids malformed navigation cases that could result in blank page behavior.
- Added styling for status notification box and inline review button.

## Implemented: Phase 2.2 Review/Edit Stability Fix
- Converted `Review / Edit` action in admin tab from query navigation to secure POST pick action with nonce.
- Selected request now opens inside same dashboard route reliably and sets admin tab state server-side.
- Added security error handling if pick-request nonce fails.

## Implemented: Phase 2.3 Admin Field Prefill Fix
- Fixed admin request form prefill logic so selected request data loads correctly after POST pick action.
- Root cause: data loading was restricted to non-POST requests, leaving fields empty on Review/Edit submit flow.

## Implemented: Phase 2.4 Blank Dashboard Visibility Fix
- Removed `reveal` class from dashboard section.
- Root cause hypothesis: when JS fails/interrupted, reveal state keeps opacity hidden and page appears blank despite header/styles loading.
- Result: dashboard content remains visible even if frontend JS has runtime issues.

## Implemented: Phase 2.5 Duplicate Submit Prevention (PRG)
- Applied Post/Redirect/Get flow for dashboard POST actions:
	- Client project submission
	- Admin request pick (`Review / Edit`)
	- Admin request update
- Moved `get_header()` to run after POST processing so redirects can execute safely before output.
- Added query-flag based success messages after redirect.
- Result: Reload no longer resubmits previous form action or duplicates requests.

## Implemented: Phase 3 Status Workflow Upgrade
- Replaced old statuses with:
	- `pending` (default after submission)
	- `processing`
	- `approved`
	- `declined`
	- `in_need`
- Admin decision model in `Admin Requests`:
	- Approve
	- Declined (requires reason; reason shown to client)
	- In Need (requires needs list)
- `In Need` behavior:
	- Admin writes needs item-by-item (dynamic field expansion while typing).
	- Client sees needs checklist in dashboard overview.
	- Client can submit partial completion; unchecked items remain pending.
	- When all needs are checked, request auto-moves to `processing`.
- `Declined` behavior:
	- Client sees decline reason in dashboard.
	- Client can edit and re-submit same request (updates existing request, no duplicate new request).
- Notification integration:
	- Status change updates continue to notify client in dashboard.

## Implemented: Phase 3.1 Professional Client Request UI
- Reworked client dashboard request display into per-request cards.
- Each request now shows:
	- Clear status badge with dedicated color
	- Request title/date
	- Status-linked details in the same card (decline reason, needs checklist, processing, approved notes)
- Removed scattered detached blocks so comments/reasons are visually attached to the correct request.
- Added polished status visuals for `pending`, `processing`, `approved`, `declined`, `in_need`.


